UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1183
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of David
2 Delvin Drake.
3 WHEREAS, David Delvin Drake was born on May 4, 1940, in Mount Sterling,
4 Kentucky, the son of Martha and Russell T. Drake; and
5 WHEREAS, a proud graduate of the University of Kentucky, David Drake earned
6 his Bachelor's Degree in Economics and pursued extensive postgraduate work before
7 beginning a long and distinguished career in public service and energy development; and
8 WHEREAS, David Drake first served as assistant industrial development director at
9 East Kentucky Power Cooperative, where his work in advancing the energy and
10 economic development of eastern Kentucky saw him travel to Hawaii on a company trip
11 where he met his future wife, Brenda; and
12 WHEREAS, David Drake went on to serve as the first secretary of the Department
13 of Energy for the Commonwealth of Kentucky, and in that role he helped shape early
14 energy policy and co-founded what would become the University of Kentucky Center for
15 Applied Energy Research (UK CAER), an institution that continues to advance
16 innovation and collaboration in the energy field; and
17 WHEREAS, returning to East Kentucky Power Cooperative in 1984, David Drake
18 concluded his career there as Business Development Manager, later continuing in a
19 consulting capacity and serving on the advisory board of UK CAER to lend his vast
20 experience to the benefit of the Commonwealth; and
21 WHEREAS, beyond his professional accomplishments, David Drake gave
22 generously of his time to civic and community service, including his tenure as a member
23 of the Lexington-Fayette Urban County Government Planning Commission, where his
24 insight and commitment to public welfare were widely respected; and
25 WHEREAS, a man guided by deep faith in all he did, David Drake was raised in
26 the Roman Catholic tradition and later found a spiritual home at Saint Michael's
27 Episcopal Church and the Episcopal Church of the Resurrection; and
Page 1 of 2
