UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1183
1 WHEREAS, David Drake was a devoted husband to his beloved wife, Brenda, a
2 loving father to his children, Russel Drake and Sheila Miracle, and a proud father-in-law
3 to Daniel Honeycutt and Eric Miracle; and
4 WHEREAS, his grandchildren, Anna, Bodhi, and Drake Miracle, brought him
5 boundless joy and pride, and he delighted in making the home he built with Brenda a
6 haven for his children and grandchildren, echoing the community his parents fostered for
7 him and his friends as a boy; and
8 WHEREAS, remembered as a man of many interests, David Drake was an avid O-
9 gauge model railroader, a builder of 1940s-era model airplanes, and a student of World
10 War II history, all pursuits that reflected his lifelong curiosity and meticulous attention to
11 detail; and
12 WHEREAS, David Drake is survived by his loving wife, Brenda; his children,
13 Russell Drake and Sheila Miracle; his sons-in-law, Daniel Honeycutt and Eric Miracle;
14 his grandchildren, Anna, Bodhi, and Drake; and his brother-in-law, Bill Burch; and
15 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth of Kentucky has lost a respected public servant, a
16 community leader, and a man whose legacy will endure in the institutions he helped to
17 build and in the hearts of all who had the privilege to know him;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The Senate extends its sincere condolences to the family, friends, and
22 community of David Delvin Drake upon his passing.
23 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
24 memory of David Delvin Drake.
25 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
26 Resolution to Senator Reginald Thomas for delivery to the family.
